column2: VARDESC
Objective Circumstances Related to Suicide Attempt  Isolation
column18: 1 = Somebody nearby, or in visual or vocal contact
column19: 2 = No one nearby or in visual or vocal contact

column2: Objective Circumstances Related to Suicide Attempt  Timing
column18: 1 = Intervention is not likely
column19: 2 = Intervention in highly unlikely

column2: Objective Circumstances Related to Suicide Attempt  Precautions against Discovery/Intervention
column18: 1 = Passive precautions (avoiding others but doing nothing to prevent intervention; alone in room with unlocked door)
column19: 2 = Active precautions (locked door)

column2: Objective Circumstances Related to Suicide Attempt  Acting to Get Help During/After Attempt
column18: 1 = Contacted but did not specifically notify potential helper regarding attempt
column19: 2 = Did not contact or notify potential helper

column2: Objective Circumstances Related to Suicide Attempt  Final Acts in Anticipation of Death (e.g., will, gifts, insurance)
column18: 1 = Thought about or made some arrangements
column19: 2 = Made definite plans or completed arrangements

column2: Objective Circumstances Related to Suicide Attempt  Active Preparation for Attempt
column18: 1 = Minimal to moderate
column19: 2 = Extensive

column2: Objective Circumstances Related to Suicide Attempt  Suicide Note
column18: 1 = Note written, but torn up; note thought about
column19: 2 = Presence of note

column2: Objective Circumstances Related to Suicide Attempt  Overt Communication of Intent Before the Attempt
column18: 1 = Equivocal communication
column19: 2 = Unequivocal communication

column2: Self-Report Alleged Purpose of Attempt
column17: 0 = To manipulate environment, get attention, revenge
column18: 1 = Components of "0" and "2"
column19: 2 = To escape, surcease, solve problems

column2: Self-Report Expectations of Fatality
column18: 1 = Thought that death was possible but not probable
column19: 2 = Thought that death was probable or certain

column2: Self-Report Conception of Method's Lethality
column17: 0 = Did less to self than he thought would be lethal
column18: 1 = Wasn't sure if what he did would be lethal
column19: 2 = Equaled or exceeded what he thought would be lethal

column2: Self-Report Seriousness of Attempt
column17: 0 = Did not seriously attempt to end life
column18: 1 = Uncertain about seriousness to end life
column19: 2 = Seriously attempted to end life

column2: Self-Report Attitude Toward Living/Dying
column18: 1 = Components of "0" and "2"
column19: 2 = Wanted to die

column2: Self-Report Conception of Medical Rescuability
column17: 0 = Thought that death would be unlikely if he received medical attention
column18: 1 = Was uncertain whether death could be averted by medical attention
column19: 2 = Was certain of death even if he received medical attention

column2: Self-Report Degree of Premeditation
column18: 1 = Suicide contemplated for three hours or less prior to attempt
column19: 2 = Suicide contemplated for more than three hours prior to attempt

column2: Other Aspects  Reaction to Attempt
column17: 0 = Sorry about attempt; feels foolish, ashamed (circle which one)
column18: 1 = Accepts both attempt and its failure
column19: 2 = Regrets failure of attempt

column2: Other Aspects  Visualization of Death
column18: 1 = Never ending sleep, darkness, end-of-things
column19: 2 = No conceptions of, or thoughts about death

column2: Other Aspects  Number of Previous Attempts
column18: 1 = One or two
column19: 2 = Three or more

column2: Other Aspects  Relationship between Alcohol Intake and Attempt
column17: 0 = Some alcohol intake prior to but not related to attempt, reportedly not enough to impair judgment, reality testing
column18: 1 = Enough alcohol intake to impair judgment, reality testing and diminish responsibility/impulse control
column19: 2 = Intentional intake of alcohol in order to facilitate implementation of suicide attempt

column2: Other Aspects  Relationship between Drug Intake and Attempt (narcotics, hallucinogens, etc. drug is not the method used to suicide)
column17: 0 = Some drug intake prior to but not related to attempt, reportedly not enough to impair judgment, reality testing
column18: 1 = Enough drug intake to impair judgment, identity testing and diminish responsibility/impulse control
column19: 2 = Intentional drug intake in order to facilitate implementation of suicide attempt
